    "body": "Don't some operating systems enforce the append bit, so that you can really only append?\r\nFrom the man page:\r\n```\r\n       a+     Open for reading and appending (writing at end of file).  The file is created if it does not exist.  The initial  file  position  for\r\n              reading is at the beginning of the file, but output is always appended to the end of the file.\r\n```\r\nI don't think that's quite what we want. For example the code to reserve space pads the file, then seeks back.",
